<p><strong>Halo Scythe</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Reapers" href="/Reapers">Reaper</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The Halo Scythe&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength">Strength</a> and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity">Dexterity</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for Faith based fighters.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>War scythe of the Cleanrot Knights who fought alongside Malenia, Blade of Miquella.</em></p> 
 <p><em>This was the weapon of commanders in Malenia's army, and the half-halo blade deals holy damage.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Halo Scythe in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The&nbsp;Halo Sycthe&nbsp;weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Drops from Scythe-wielding <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lesser Cleanrot Knight" href="/Lesser+Cleanrot+Knight">Lesser Cleanrot Knights</a>&nbsp;just south of the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=3209&amp;lat=-180.53125&amp;lng=143.75802&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=3209&amp;lat=-180.53125&amp;lng=143.75802&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Heart of Aeonia</a>&nbsp;near&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=1560&amp;lat=-181.29687&amp;lng=143.75635&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=1560&amp;lat=-181.29687&amp;lng=143.75635&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Commander O'Neil</a>. (rare drop)</li> 
 <li>there are two different types of Cleanrot Knights near the Heart of Aeonia. The ones already patrolling the&nbsp;area are wielding Halo Scythes and the ones that rise up from the waters are wielding Cleanrot Spears, each weapon only drops from its respective knight type, so only&nbsp;farm the ones you need.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Halo Scythe Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Miquella's Ring of Light" href="/Miquella's+Ring+of+Light">Miquella's Ring of Light</a> 
  <ul> 
   <li>Your character swings the scythe from left to right, releasing a horizontal wheel or halo of light, which hovers in place for a moment before shooting forward.</li> 
   <li>The halo deals holy damage and scales only with faith.</li> 
   <li>You can chain cast the halos as long as you have FP and stamina. However, it should be noted that your weapon will not connect with enemies when using the weapon skill.</li> 
   <li>The halos will not track down moving enemies.</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with Ashes of War or Buffed.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li><strong>The Halo Scythe</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones">Somber Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>While the Ash of War has a lengthy wind-up and a delayed projectile, the weapon portion (after&nbsp;the 1.07 buff) connects with enemies,&nbsp;providing additional damage - about 25% of a light attack - and Blood loss Buildup at close range.</li> 
 <li>Causes&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Hemorrhage" href="/Hemorrhage">Blood loss</a>&nbsp;Buildup:&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Hemorrhage" href="/Hemorrhage"><img title="Causes Blood Loss Buildup" src="/file/Elden-Ring/hemmorage.png" alt="hemmorage" width="18">&nbsp;(55)</a>.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;200</li> 
 <li>Anti-block: ignores 40% damage negation from blocks, heavy- and charge attacks ignores more</li> 
 <li>Base drop rate is&nbsp;2% (at 100 Discovery)</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;</p> 
